00:01:33.670 --> 00:01:36.080
- So there's something
about being in the presence

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:37.550
of another human being

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:40.030
and watching the eyes and
watching the movements

00:01:40.030 --> 00:01:42.290
and paying attention to
what that person is doing.

00:01:42.290 --> 00:01:46.463
That social context is
extremely important to learning.

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:49.720
- Because, I mean...

00:01:49.720 --> 00:01:51.510
- Get the chunks of candy.

00:01:51.510 --> 00:01:53.830
- We can see it in school-aged children

00:01:53.830 --> 00:01:56.500
who use the social brain
when they're interacting

00:01:56.500 --> 00:01:58.300
with one another to collaborate,

00:01:58.300 --> 00:02:00.880
when they're studying how
another person goes at it,

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:04.000
when they're watching the
eyes even unconsciously

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:07.910
of their study partner to work
towards a solution together.

00:02:07.910 --> 00:02:09.850
In fact, I like to say the social brain

00:02:09.850 --> 00:02:11.700
gates human learning.

00:02:11.700 --> 00:02:14.800
That without the
motivation and information

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:16.470
provided by the social brain,

00:02:16.470 --> 00:02:19.080
learning just doesn't
take off in the same way

00:02:19.080 --> 00:02:22.423
that it does when the
social brain is engaged.

